*1x 1.3 mm hex key/driver

===== How to assemble the cylindrical lens system =====

Take both components out of their respective boxes, and after taking the Ø1" external threaded ring out, put the lens inside the mount with its arrow on the banding pointing in the direction of the light path. Use the [http://www.thorlabs.de/thorProduct.cfm?partNumber=SPW602 SPW602] or [http://www.thorlabs.de/thorProduct.cfm?partNumber=SPW606 SPW606] to put the ring back into the threading and tighten until the lens does not move. 

Align the rotation using a 1.3 mm hex key/driver by loosening the two screws on the front face of the rotational mount and rotate the face plate (not the mount) until it is in the correct position relative to the orientation of the cylindrical lens. Tighten the two front face screws down one the desired position is reached.

